The article emphasizes the importance of blood donation, particularly during the coronavirus pandemic. It highlights that every 2 seconds, someone in the US needs a blood transfusion. Due to the hardships caused by the virus, the country's blood and platelet supply has reached critical levels. Over 30,000 blood drives have been canceled since mid-March, putting those with severe illnesses or involved in life-threatening accidents at risk of not receiving the necessary care. Many blood banks have depleted stocks, with Type O blood being especially crucial as it can meet the needs of any patient. The article urges healthy individuals to donate blood at local centers, assuring that special protocols are in place to protect donors from possible infection. The First Lady and the author express gratitude to blood donors and those involved in facilitating donations, recognizing their contribution to America's health and well-being.